claim.claim-text:
9. A DNA analysis system, comprising:
a substrate having a plurality of etched channels;
a first laser and a second laser that simultaneously irradiate distinct areas of the substrate, the substrate having a plurality of labeled analytes, the labeled analytes labeled with one of at least four distinct markers that emit distinct emission wavelength or wavelength ranges relative to one another;
at least 4 distinct cameras such that each camera detects a distinct emission wavelength or wavelength range corresponding to one of the distinct markers; and
a TDI system that processes signals detected by the cameras.

19. A system for detecting fluorescent signals, comprising:
a substrate having a plurality of channels;
the substrate having a plurality of fluorescently labeled polynucleotides disposed thereon;
a first camera and a second camera that detect at least a first fluorescent signal from a first area of the substrate and simultaneously detects at least a second fluorescent signal from a second area of the substrate, respectively, the first and second areas spatially offset from one another; and
a processor that receives data relating to the first and second signals, and further generates data relating to an identity of at least one nucleotide of a polynucleotide in the first area of the substrate and data relating to an identity of at least one nucleotide of a polynucleotide in the second area of the substrate.
